casebody.data:
Kohlmann, Respondent, v. Minicus, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. January 4, 1892.) Appeal from fourth district court. Action by Louis Kohlmann against Louis Minicus.

Argued before Bookstaver, Bischoff, and Pryor, JJ.

W. R. Eeese, for appellant. IV. F. Browne, for respondent.

No opinion. Judgment reversed, new trial ordered, costs to appellant to abide the event.
